    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1888-01-19T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1888-01-19T00:00:00-05:00" n="281"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d281">
                <head>No. 994.<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Bayard</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">de Muruaga</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1888-01-19">
                            <hi rend="italic">January</hi> 19, 1888</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to acknowledge the receipt of
                    your note of the 10th instant, communicating information of measures to be taken
                    by your Government in favor of the wine product, and especially inquiring if
                    this Government would be disposed to participate in an international congress at
                    Madrid to consider the general subject.</p>
                <p>The proposal of the Government of Her Majesty the Queen Regent is one of great
                    importance, upon which this Government would not wish to act except in
                    accordance with the wishes of Congress, but before ascertaining the views of
                    that body thereon, it is thought advisable to consult with the Commissioner of
                    Agriculture, in whose especial charge the wine-growing interests of the United
                    States are placed, to whom accordingly a copy of your note has been
                    transmitted.</p>
                <p>Accept, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">T. F. Bayard.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
